{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents mRNA interferase HigB from Escherichia coli and similar bacterial proteins. HigB is the toxin of the HigB-HigA toxin-antitoxin (TA) system, acting as a translation-dependent mRNA interferase. HigB inhibits protein synthesis by cleaving translated mRNAs within the coding region [[cite:PUB00054169], [cite:PUB00100106]]. The crystal structure of this TA complex shows an hetero-tetramer formed by two HigB and two HigA subunits. Each toxin HigB has a microbial RNase T1 fold with a three antiparallel β-sheet core shielded by a few α-helices at either side [[cite:PUB00088843]]. Unlike other TA systems, both components make minimal interactions [[cite:PUB00100108]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF09907" "HigB_toxin, RelE-like toxic component of a toxin-antitoxin system"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Toxin-antitoxin system, mRNA interferase HigB", "short" "Toxin_HigB"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 4, "domain_architectures" 7, "proteomes" 1046, "taxa" 6720, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 7745, "sets" 0, "proteins" 7743, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 5844}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR018669", :literature {"PUB00054169" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Christensen-Dalsgaard M" "Jorgensen MG" "Gerdes K."], "ISO_journal" "Mol. Microbiol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2958.2009.06969.x", "medline_journal" "Mol Microbiol", "title" "Three new RelE-homologous mRNA interferases of Escherichia coli differentially induced by environmental stresses.", "year" 2010, "raw_pages" "333-48", "volume" "75", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 19943910}, "PUB00100108" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Schureck MA" "Maehigashi T" "Miles SJ" "Marquez J" "Cho SE" "Erd